                                                                                                    <div><h2>Enabling MMS on iPhone 3G and iPhone 3GS</h2></div>
                        <div><div class="attr HOW_TO">
<p>AT&amp;T MMS requires iPhone OS 3.1 or later and a carrier-settings update. Use these steps to update your iPhone to the latest iPhone OS and carrier settings:</p>
<ol>
<li>Make sure that you have a working Internet connection on your computer and that you are using iTunes 8.2 or later.</li>
<li>Connect iPhone to the computer and open iTunes.</li>
<li>Select your iPhone in the Devices list and click "Check for Update".
<ul>
<li>Update to iPhone OS 3.1 or later if prompted to do so.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Click "Download and Update" when prompted.<br />
<img alt="[Update Settings Screenshot]" vspace="10" src="library/APPLE/APPLECARE_ALLGEOS/HT3880/HT3880-01_iphoneos31_update_en_002.png" width="490" height="162" /></li>
<li>When the update is complete, you will see the following screen:<br />
<img alt="[Update Successful Screenshot]" vspace="10" src="library/APPLE/APPLECARE_ALLGEOS/HT3880/HT3880-02_iphoneos31_success_en_002.png" width="474" height="146" /></li>
<li>On your iPhone, open Messages. You should see the camera icon to the left of the text field:<br />
<img alt="[Text Field Screenshot]" vspace="10" src="library/APPLE/APPLECARE_ALLGEOS/HT3880/HT3880-03_iphoneos31_text-field_en_002.png" width="320" height="48" /><br />
If you do not see the camera icon, restart your iPhone.
<ul>
<li>Hold the power button until "slide to power off" appears. Slide to power off your device. When it is off, press the power button to turn it back on.</li>
<li>After iPhone restarts, open Messages to check for the camera icon.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p>For more information on using MMS, see the <a onclick='s_objectID="support/country/?dest=manuals_1";return this.s_oc?this.s_oc(e):true' href="support/country/?dest=manuals">iPhone User Guide</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="attr ADDITIONAL_INFORMATION">
<h2>Additional Information</h2>
<p>If you are unable to enable MMS after following the above steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>Disconnect and reconnect your iPhone and try again.</li>
<li>Verify that you are using iPhone OS 3.1 or later.</li>
<li>Refer to&#160;<a onclick='s_objectID="kb/TS2755_1";return this.s_oc?this.s_oc(e):true' href="kb/TS2755">iPhone 3G: Troubleshooting MMS</a> for assistance.</li>
<li>If the issue persists, contact <a onclick='s_objectID="support/_1";return this.s_oc?this.s_oc(e):true' href="support/">AT&amp;T</a>.</li>
</ol>
<p>If you see a red exclamation mark when sending an MMS message, refer to&#160;<a onclick='s_objectID="kb/TS2755_2";return this.s_oc?this.s_oc(e):true' href="kb/TS2755">iPhone 3G: Troubleshooting MMS</a> for assistance.</p>
</div>

</div>
